{
  "title": "FastAPI Package for REST APIs in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to create and deploy a simple REST API using FastAPI, a modern, fast (high-performance), web framework for building APIs with Python 3.12+.",
  "key_points": [
    "Install required packages: FastAPI, Uvicorn, and Python 3.12 or above.",
    "Create a new FastAPI application by importing the FastAPI module and initializing an instance.",
    "Define API endpoints using route decorators such as @app.get(), @app.post(), etc.",
    "Write your API functionality within the defined routes using Python 3.12+ syntax.",
    "Run your FastAPI application using Uvicorn, which provides an ASGI server and automatically detects changes for hot-reloading.",
    "Deploy your REST API by building a Docker image or hosting on platforms like Heroku, AWS, Google Cloud, etc."
  ],
  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI\nimport uvicorn\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.get('/')\ndef main():\n    return {'Hello': 'World'} \n\nif __name__ == "__main__":\n    uvicorn.run(app, host='127.0.0.1', port=8000)\n```"
    }
  ],
  "version_notes": [
    "Python 3.12+ is required for FastAPI to utilize its improved performance benefits.",
    "FastAPI v0.69.0 and Uvicorn v0.15.0 are the latest versions at the time of writing."
  ],
  "caveats": [
    "Remember to handle exceptions appropriately in your routes.",
    "Test your API thoroughly using tools like Pytest or FastAPI's built-in testing features."
  ]
}
